snippet: Central banks’ decisions to pump more money into the global economy have spurred a stock rally. But some advisers see the moves as just a successful trip to the emergency room.
abstract: Central banks’ decisions to pump more money into the global economy have spurred a stock rally; some advisers, however, contend that neither the economy nor the stock market is out of the woods; many mutual fund investors seem to want to move in to the market, but are wary that it will face additional issues, including inflation.
lead_paragraph: Central banks’ decisions to pump more money into the global economy have spurred a stock rally. But some advisers see the moves as just a successful trip to the emergency room.

headline.seo: Mutual Fund Investors, Flying Again but Feeling Dizzy
headline.main: Mutual Fund Investors, Flying Again but Feeling Dizzy
